Task 2 -- Build Your Student Digital Portfolio

	Platforms I Chose:
o	GitHub : a platform for hosting, sharing, and collaborating on coding projects using version control
o	LinkedIn : a professional networking site for building an online career profile and connecting with industry professionals
o	Stack Overflow:  a community-driven Q&A platform where developers ask and answer programming-related questions

	What Each One Is Used For:
o	GitHub is used to store code repositories, showcase projects, and collaborate with other developers worldwide
o	LinkedIn is used to display academic achievements, skills, internships, and professional experiences to potential employers
o	Stack Overflow is used to solve coding problems, learn from experienced developers, and contribute answers to the tech community

	How I Plan to Use Them Over the Next Four Years:
o	GitHub regularly upload class projects, personal coding exercises, and collaborative work to build a strong portfolio
o	LinkedIn progressively update my profile with internships, certifications, and achievements each year to attract future employers
o	Stack Overflow actively use it to troubleshoot coding challenges during studies, and eventually contribute answers as my skills grow
o	By graduation, these three platforms will collectively serve as a living digital resume showcasing my technical growth and professional readiness

